t in the single-case study.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aPsychoanalysisxEvaluation. 0aPsychoanalysisxResearch. 0aPsychotherapyxOutcome assessment. 7aPSYCHOLOGY / Movements / Psychoanalysis.2bisacsh1 aBachrach, Henry, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aSkolnikoff, Alan, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aWaldron, Sherwood, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030014615840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300146158423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300146158/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles